00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:01.670
So I'm submitting stacked PRs all the time, and

00:07:01.910 --> 00:07:03.000
this is one of them.

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:06.830
Maybe you'll notice that usually when you have a PR in

00:07:06.830 --> 00:07:11.710
GitHub or anywhere else, the convention is that you want everything

00:07:11.710 --> 00:07:14.100
in one massive commit, so that your commit history isn't

00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:15.000
horrible after the fact.

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:18.140
Which means that when you're trying to push big features,

00:07:18.140 --> 00:07:20.990
you have to make them entirely separate PRs, and then

00:07:20.990 --> 00:07:23.000
you kind of lose what's going on.

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:27.410
You have to have issue trackers or actual full-on

00:07:27.410 --> 00:07:31.990
tracking apps separately from your Git forge.

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:35.120
Or you have it in one massive PR, and that is

00:07:35.120 --> 00:07:39.140
also just like a monster PR that takes weeks or months to

00:07:39.140 --> 00:07:40.990
review all in one go.

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:43.790
So what stacked PRs gives you is that you can kind

00:07:43.910 --> 00:07:47.590
of chunk things into each commit being its own like separate mini

00:07:47.590 --> 00:07:49.990
PR, and you can go through them one by one.

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:52.000
You can merge a subset of them if you like.

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:57.140
So if we said that we like everything up to 1137

00:07:57.140 --> 00:07:59.330
there, we could just merge all of those and then continue

00:07:59.330 --> 00:08:01.130
on the rest of them if we weren't so sure about

00:08:01.130 --> 00:08:02.000
the rest of them.

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:04.000
We can clear them one by one.

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:07.550
It kind of forces me, the submitter of the stacked

00:08:07.790 --> 00:08:12.000
PR, to also break up my commits into logical chunks.

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:15.260
I think some people do it like chronologically speaking, but

00:08:15.260 --> 00:08:19.590
I think that the dimensionality personally for me, how I

00:08:19.590 --> 00:08:22.850
've been doing it, is that any one of them could

00:08:22.850 --> 00:08:26.000
be merged like semi-independently of one another.

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:28.750
But currently stacked PRs can only be merged bottom to top

00:08:28.910 --> 00:08:29.000
.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:34.990
So yeah, that's one value add as an example.

