00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:14.210
So a PDS is where you store your data, and

00:10:14.310 --> 00:10:17.090
then that then goes on and makes a write-esque,

00:10:17.090 --> 00:10:21.520
in quotation marks, request to a relay, which then kind

00:10:21.520 --> 00:10:26.010
of caches in a time-based cache and forwards it

00:10:26.010 --> 00:10:28.000
onto an app view.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:31.190
You've got like stacked boxes for everything that can have,

00:10:31.190 --> 00:10:33.000
you know, one million of them.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:36.010
But in the blue sky infrastructure, you only have one app

00:10:36.040 --> 00:10:38.000
view, so there's no stack there.

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:41.710
And then your PDS forwards on read requests to that app

00:10:41.790 --> 00:10:45.400
view that then has like a pool, like a full cache

00:10:45.620 --> 00:10:46.000
.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:50.150
And why I said app view like is that I wanted to

00:10:50.310 --> 00:10:54.990
include Red Dwarf from the get-go.

00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:57.920
So Red Dwarf is like an app view list,

00:10:57.920 --> 00:11:02.480
quote unquote, app view, and just kind of uses F

00:11:02.480 --> 00:11:06.280
IG's microcosm tools in lieu of an app view

00:11:06.280 --> 00:11:07.000
proper.

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.490
So it's a lot easier to run, a lot cheaper

00:11:09.910 --> 00:11:10.000
.

00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:12.490
